.TH YTRAN 1 "2026-04-14" "ytran 1.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ytran \- fetch and summarize YouTube video transcripts
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ytran
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RI [ VIDEO_URL_OR_ID " ..." ]
.br
.B ytran
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RI CHANNEL_URL
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ytran
fetches YouTube video transcripts via transcriptapi.com, formats them
with Claude, generates summaries, and stores everything in a local
SQLite database.
.PP
When given a channel URL (containing \fB/@\fR, \fB/channel/\fR, \fB/c/\fR,
or \fB/user/\fR), the tool expands the full video list via
.BR yt\-dlp ,
skips already-downloaded videos, and processes the remainder with
automatic retry and exponential backoff.
.PP
Multiple video URLs are also processed in batch mode with backoff.
Failed downloads are re-queued at the back of the list (circular queue)
and retried until 4 consecutive failures at the backoff ceiling.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-browse
Open an interactive browser for the transcript database after processing
any URLs given on the command line.
If invoked with no arguments,
.B \-\-browse
is implied.
Options and URLs may be intermixed in any order.
.TP
.B \-\-fix
Scan all database entries and fill in any missing fields (metadata,
transcripts, summaries).
Uses circular retry queue with backoff for transient failures.
Entries saved with
.B \-\-no\-summary
are skipped; use
.B \-\-fix\-full
to include them.
.TP
.B \-\-fix\-full
Like
.BR \-\-fix ,
but includes raw\-only entries (those saved with
.BR \-\-no\-summary ).
The raw\-only flag is cleared and summaries are generated.
.PP
When given video URLs or IDs as arguments, only those specific
videos are processed.
Without arguments, the entire database is scanned.
Multiple videos use batch mode with backoff.
.TP
.BI \-\-max\-backoff " SECS"
Backoff ceiling in seconds for batch/fix/channel modes.
Default: 1800 (30 minutes).
.TP
.BI \-\-min\-delay " SECS"
Minimum delay between requests in batch modes.
Default: 5.
.TP
.BI \-\-initial\-delay " SECS"
Starting delay between requests in batch modes.
Default: 10.
.TP
.B \-\-haiku
Use claude-haiku-4-5 for formatting and summarization.
Shorthand for
.BR "\-\-model claude-haiku-4-5" .
.TP
.B \-\-sonnet
Use claude-sonnet-4-6 for formatting and summarization (default).
Shorthand for
.BR "\-\-model claude-sonnet-4-6" .
.TP
.BI \-\-model " MODEL"
Claude model to use for formatting and summarization.
Default: claude-sonnet-4-6.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-no\-summary
Fetch metadata and raw transcript only; do not format or summarize
with Claude.
The entry is flagged as raw\-only so that future
.B \-\-fix
runs leave it alone.
Does not require an Anthropic API key.
.TP
.BI \-\-skip " ID1,ID2,..."
Comma-separated list of video IDs to skip during \-\-fix operations.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.SH BATCH MODES
.PP
Three modes use the circular retry queue with AIMD
(additive decrease, multiplicative increase) backoff:
.TP
.B \-\-fix
Re-queues transient failures; marks permanent failures in the database.
Resumes from last position on restart via the
.I queue_state
table.
.TP
.B Channel URLs
Expands channel playlists via
.BR yt\-dlp (1),
filters already-downloaded videos, then processes the remainder.
Transcripts are fetched in
.B \-\-no\-summary
mode.
.TP
.B Multiple video URLs
Two or more video URLs on the command line trigger batch processing
with backoff.
.PP
On success, the delay decreases by 2 seconds (floor:
.BR \-\-min\-delay ).
On failure, the delay triples (ceiling:
.BR \-\-max\-backoff ).
After 4 consecutive failures at the ceiling, the tool gives up and
marks remaining videos with the last error detail.
.PP
Ctrl-C during batch processing saves the cursor position so the
next run resumes where it left off.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/ytran/youtube-transcripts.db
Default database location (respects $XDG_DATA_HOME).
.TP
.I ~/.youtubetotranscript_api_key
transcriptapi.com bearer token.
.TP
.I ~/.anthropic_api_key
Anthropic API key for Claude.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR yt\-dlp (1)
\(em used for expanding channel URLs to video lists.
